<Author>GreatDaneNo1
<Content>hotel with a bit of a difference Great location- very central, yet off the main street. Also close to good restaurants and clubs.This is not your standard holiday inn/carpet everywhere type hotel- every room is different and the building is what they call an altbau in Germany (not purpose built, but used to be flats) so it has lovely spacious rooms with high ceilings. Nice to have something other than landscapes on the walls, too (mostly artworks of males) Only downside is that it can be a bit noisy at timesI really enjoyed the breakfast, too. 
