<Author>Jono_UK
<Content>Rude owners, noisy This was my worse experience in a gay owned BB. Avoid.The description in TimeOut guide to Berlin (page 209, 2004 edition) says 'comfortable rooms' and 'sumptuous breakfast'. Neither is the case.1) Breakfast is OK, but far from sumptuous, with bread rolls whose crust is hard as rock - 100 miles removed from traditional, nice German bread2) The main problem however is not breakfast, but the rooms. They are spacious, but incredibly noisy. There is an incredible amount of noise coming from both inside and outside the hotel.Inside the hotel, the corridor floors are creaky and the doors badly insulated for corridor noise, which means that from about 7 am one can hear people milling around outside the room on their way to breakfast.Much worse, street noise is strong, but also there is a night club on the ground floor, whose thumping music resonates in the rooms. We had to sleep with earplugs. Hardly what you would call 'comfortable'3) To compound it all, apart from one member of staff, service is at best uninterested, at worse rude. After the first night I complained about the noise and said I wanted to move out. Because I had paid for 3 nights on arrival, I wanted a refund of the unused two nights. The owner suddenly became very angry, made comments on the verge of racism (which country do you come from?) and called me stupid for wanting a refund. It was their terms and conditions, and if I didn't like it, tough, but I would have to forfeit two nights' payment 
