<Author>tritiumnyc
<Content>ArtHotel is unqiue and wild, but not the best nights sleep I've stayed at the ArtHotel a number of times. I must say, in many senses it is a wonderful and unique place that caters to gay men who aren't afraid to have fun. In another sense, the place is a bit crude. The rooms are colorful but the floors are often cracked and clean but poorly kept. There tend to be reasonable sized cracks in the bedroom door leaving you to hear footstep taken down the hall. This is praticularly bad because many of the guests at ArtHotel tend to be larger men wearing leather boots comming back from a good night out. Suffice to say, they have HEAVY steps.The younger guy that works there tends to be very nice and as helpful as he can be. The proprieter who is always dressed in leather can be rude, disrespectful and egotsitc at times. I've never had serious confrontations, but I've been made to feel like I was a loathly pion in his great empire on a number of occassions. The ArtHotel has an apartment room that isn't bad because it has a seperate entrance and you don't have to deal with foot traffic. I'd stay here again if I wanted a hot room to have kinky sex in. I'd not stay here to get good sleep and enjoy something that's actually nice. 
