<Author>Weinesq
<Content>Central Location -- Very Clean I have to say I am really glad I stayed here. It is a very central location to the gay area and the U train. It is also walking distance to the huge amazing department store. Having the club downstairs was fun -- easy access to boys. There is also a great bar next door with lots of cute/30 something guys. The boys in the bar under the hotel were a bit twinky. Easy access to 'fun' -- it was never more than a few mins away. Sauna/video places. Bars. You name it. Upon check in I was given a mag with a list of everything happening in the city. The bathroom was the smallest I have ever seen but I was only in there to shower. The shower had great pressure. The bed was more comfortable than it looked. It was sort of hospital bed-ish but when you are exhausted...it doesnt matter. The hotel was ALWAYS clean and breakfast was always served on time. I have to say staying here really made it easy to get my bearings.Also found a great tour guide. 7 hour tour for 70 dollars. Look him up at hotmal -- sfwanderer (Tom) made berlin come alive for me. 
