<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>don't ever stay here Travelled here during May 2006 and spent 5 nights in the Art Hotel Connections, Fruggerstasse 33, Berlin, located just above the connections gay disco and garage fetish shop.I could sum up this experience in two simple words: NEVER AGAINHowever, for the benefit of the reading public, gay travellers, respectable people and in particular gay respectable professional well travelled couples, then i'll say a bit more.The decor is poor...an kind of dingy dark salmonly colour adorns the walls. the carpets are tacked down for some reason running up the centre of the hallway floors. The room was small with a modest wardrope that had a very awkward stiff door. The bedroom door was also very awkward to open and we skint our knuckles opening it from the outside most days. There were no drawers or other places of storage for your clothes/belongings.On arrival, Leonardo the owner, meets you in all his leathers (which is fine) but for some reason seems to insist on feeling you up.....!!Breakfast was laughable. Sure there's some cereal, very watery orange juice, some cold meats and luke warm potatoes...........however try and get a boiled egg and you'd have to queue at the breakfast room from about 4am.......as, for some reason, they only seem to make 3 or 4 boiled eggs.......for about 15 guests!! Ask for another one to be made so that you can actually have one...and you get a -25C frosty reception, a huff, sigh, bit of sulking and stomping.......then you might get one...boiled for all of 30 seconds and unedible.Every floor board in the entire hotel seems to creek at about 60 decibells.......so with all the coming and going day and night..then it's kinda hard to get a decent sleep / rest....i'm actually home now for a rest !Ask if they can book you the private transfer to the airport (chauffeur service - which is good actually), then you get the same huffing, sighing and stomping response as mentioned above.Often when we go on trips, we come back and recommend hotels, places or countries to our friends, families, colleagues etc.....however this hotel will certainly not be mentioned to anyone in this regard.....quite the opposite infact.I believe in supporting gay owned businesses or ventures.........just the same as i believe in supporting gay friendly businesses......however i also believe in high quality standards when paying good money for services and accommodation......i never mind paying for quality. Here at Art Hotel Connections you are most definetly ripped off for your pink pound and i will in future spend my money in a large multi national hotel chain.......who will undoubtedbly have higher room and general hotel standards.....and probably much better breakfasts (which wouldn't be difficult).And when one mentions these above complaints to Leonardo, the leather clad owner, you are met with a shrug and a pigeon english reply basically making out that he doesn't really understand or cant be bothered! Do yourself a favour and stay in a more mainstream hotel....all of which by the way are very gay friendly and have far far higher standards in all respects. My overall rating = 1/10....( and the 1point is only cos it gave us somewhere to leave our stuff and sleep). Very disappointed at the gay community ripping off the gay clients! 
