<Author>jdbhouston
<Content>Disappointed Having visited the Art Hotel Connection in 2002, I was looking forward to going there again on a recent trip with a friend who had never been to Berlin. I knew it was in a great location, near several gay clubs, as well as a short walk away from the massive KaDeWa department store. I was disappointed, and a bit embarrassed, to find that it was not as pleasant as I had remembered. Although the room was relatively clean, it was in need of a good dusting. The switch on the lamp next to my bed was broken, so I had to take it apart to turn the lamp on and off. The bathroom was tiny, even as compared to small bathrooms in other European hotels, so small that I had to leave the bathroom door ajar when I brushed my teeth. To cap it off, one evening as we were heading out to the clubs, the doorknob fell off in my hand! If I ever have the opportunity to visit Berlin again, I am sorry to say I won't likely be staying here. 
