<Author>Beetleman
<Content>Good hotel in great location We stayed here in early September 2004 for five nights. In general it was a very good experience. The room was quite large especially for Europe standards and for a reasonable price (90 Euros/night for reserving early). The bathroom was tiny, tiny, tiny but workable. The included buffet breakfast was quite generous with bread, cheese, cold cuts. The location for us was outstanding as it's right in the center of one of Berlin's gay villages. We even had a balcony onto the street. Staff was always helpful. We were a tad disappointed with the internet access which wasn't always available and had an annoying keyboard. Would we stay there again though? Quite likely. 
